<div id="review_3766922553" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3766922553" />
    <a title="James Carter" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10226772-james-carter"><img alt="James Carter" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1548893405p2/10226772.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3766922553?book_show_action=true">Jan 12, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="James Carter" class="user" itemprop="url" name="James Carter" href="/user/show/10226772-james-carter">James Carter</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780671550295" href="/book/show/137967.The_Starlight_Crystal">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3766922553" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3266570678640241278">This is not a satisfying read in the traditional sense. It’s a very out dated book by today’s information and doesn’t particularly make any real sense but for reasons that are probably purely nostalgic and sentimental, I love it. I was 11 years old when I read this book and I used books to escape a pretty dark childhood. I think the romanticism of a love story that lasts infinitely and repeats forever impacted me the most. The man I am today knows the kid who read this book NEEDED to read a love</span>
  <span id="freeText3266570678640241278" style="display:none">This is not a satisfying read in the traditional sense. It’s a very out dated book by today’s information and doesn’t particularly make any real sense but for reasons that are probably purely nostalgic and sentimental, I love it. I was 11 years old when I read this book and I used books to escape a pretty dark childhood. I think the romanticism of a love story that lasts infinitely and repeats forever impacted me the most. The man I am today knows the kid who read this book NEEDED to read a love story like that otherwise I might have missed out in believing in it at all. Maybe that is why despite this books flaws it has remained a fond memory. Having just finished reading it again, I can see why the young man I was always refused to let ago of it. It’s not about how good the book is, it’s about the way the book made me feel and now makes me feel. </span>
  <a data-text-id="3266570678640241278" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


